metadata.name: Extreme Ways #201
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.name: miniGlyph #73
metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: unbuilt #53
metadata.description:
This is a journey through architecture that never existed.

Inspired by the grammatical rules behind French sacral architecture of the Middle Ages, this generative tool is meant for creating a collection of 256 plans of fictional buildings. Each plan is a unique variation on semantic relations between architectural elements: from a regular composition resembling existing churches to a dynamic aggregation of vaults, columns and chevets. But always following the same set of rules extracted from multiple examples of gothic cathedrals.

Every church has its place and time in which it could have been built in an alternative series of historical events.

This artistic tribute to the research of Stiny and Mitchell about Palladian architecture or Duarte's work about Siza takes the topic of formalizing architectural language onto a lighthearted level by moving it to a slightly imaginary world.

To zoom, press a mouse button when over the image or touch the screen. To pan, keep the mouse pressed and move it around.

metadata.name: SoulSea #139
metadata.description:
The Soul Sea

You look down and find that the ocean in your heart is a sine wave. 
The tide gently laps onto the shore.

The soul is the sea. You are the land. 
There are waves on the shore, and the waves are slices.

Gazing at the slices, you feel the coldness of the Arctic Ocean, the permafrost of the Antarctic Sea, the deep darkness of the bottomless sea.

Stay silent, hear the sound of the waves lapping at the innumerable shores far away.
Feel the soul of the digital ocean.

Interactivities:
> Key P: Pause
> Key S: Save
> Press and move mouseX: wave moves slower / faster

Che-Yu Wu
